Great food at an unbeatable price. Recently took a friend from Canada here; we both got platters and soft drinks and left with a $31 bill including a 20% tip. I highly recommend the Gryo! Staff was very friendly and we didn’t once feel pressured during our 3-hour meal and chat. Definitely coming back here!

Very good traditional med fare. Atmosphere is lacking, but they make up for it with friendly service. Entree prices are very competitive for the area, and portion sizes are good. The place could use some sprucing up. Overall I would recommend, especially for lunch.
Best falafel in DC.
Nicest guys and great food!

Food portions were large and the staff was friendly.  The order was made quickly and we were in an out within 10 minutes.  I wish there were more options available -- it looks like they are falling into the amazon/uber/grubhub vortex where they are being told to make more "american" foods such as pizza/burgers/fried etc... I definitely liked the food and hope they can refocus on what makes them great
The best food ever!

The gyro appeared old and was dry and hard.  The grape leaves were horrible (I'm not sure HOW they received such great reviews, unless I just had a bad batch). The falafels and hummus were tasty, thus the 2 stars. Maybe this was a bad day for the restaurant.

Mediterranean Spot isn't gourmet dining, but it does serve great food for what the restaurant is: a casual joint that provides middle eastern-style fare in generous portions at very reasonable prices (for DC). As others have mentioned, the place is clean and the staff are attentive and friendly.
Great grape Vines in this mostly food to go to go place.

Ate some of the best gyros I’ve ever had, for a very reasonable price (~$12 for a wrap).  The service was questionable to say the least, but the owner was super nice and the food was amazing.  Definitely recommend stopping by
A nice and delicious food!
Awesome

Decent food. Friendly service. Large portions
Excellent.   Great home made food, in a great little spot.  Perfect name.

I'm kind of surprised by the amount of positive reviews, which brought me there. My hopes for tasty Mediterranean food were misplaced.  The pros: the staff is amazingly kind and the portions are huge, which gives value for money  But beyond that it was disappointing- the food was literally microwaved. I got the falafel and found the taste wholly underwhelming. My Egyptian friend got the Shawarma and was equally unimpressed. The place smelled funny too- in a stuffy, moldy way. With so many good and affordable Meditarranean food in the area, I have no reason to recommend this one.
I like the food and the service very nice very clean,soft music

My WHOLE meal was fantastic. The grape leaves were on point, the hummus was some of the best I've ever had, my shawarma combo was fantastic, and more food than I needed. I don't live in DC, but when I visit again I would love to come here. The gentleman that ran the place served us, and cooked. He was attentive, on point, and friendly. Excellent food and customer service.
The best schwarma in town, and the nicest staff, too. Can't say enough good things about The Spot!
The food is great and the owners are very nice!
Stunning food and a great cook. Very good Falafel wraps, one of the best in DC.. More people should try it out

Stopped in here really quick on our way to the drum circle at Meridian Hill Park. We had smoothies (green and mango) as well as chicken salads- everything was delicious!  The owners were also SO sweet. Really enjoyed chatting with them. Great experience. 🤗
This was literally the best food I loved the steak such a great taste to it love the whole bowl of chicken and rise and beans definatily check out the place I’d recommend the steak 🤤🤤

The food is wholesome, delicious and healthy. It is handicap accessible. The menu is unique in that you can order vegan or non vegan and the food is Mediterranean and mideastern. Great place for tea, coffee and dessert. There is a full service bar and wonderful service.
It's a great place to go I highly recommended
Love the food and yes check out the new cool bar open now!

I've been many places in the Med/Eastern Europe (Crete, Greece, Haifa, Turkey, etc.) and have had a lot of schwarma...this place does food just as good, or better, than any place I ate in the Med. Highly recommend! Great food and great service, at a very reasonable price!

Kabobs are pretty good, but you will probably be waiting for some time. Getting there can be troublesome, parking is extremely difficult most of the time, and the prices are somewhat high, but they're about right for downtown DC. Get ready to empty your pockets but fill your stomach.

This place is highly underrated. Me and my friends had a Falafel and a Beef dish. My friend had the beef dish and enjoyed it a lot and so did I with the Falafel, that came with rice. I don't know why it doesn't get more crowd as the food is really good.

Granted I've only been here when I'm wasted. The price for the amount of food you get is unbeatable. I always get the shwarma combo platter and never regret it. The meats are juicy and you can't beat the veggies that come with it. Metered parking outside

This is my go to spot after a night out on U st. It's never busy and the food is both tasty and affordable, which is great after you've spent so much money on drinks. I took my roommates here for the first time and they're in love with it.
Awesome place to eat with family and friends... Great food and customer service.
Great Sharma plate!!!

We were only people in the place yet food was slow and when we got home realized they messed up our order. This happened even after we checked.  Menu wasn't clear on what came with the dish, and staff was rude when we questioned them about the menu. Gyro meat was ok, but I like mine crispy, and this was not. Chicken tasted like fish and was under cooked.  Had to throw it out. While I don't have high expectations for late night food, thiscwad just bad. Maybe an off night? I won't go back to find out.

The gyros are the best in the city. Muhomed and his wife Ababa are gracious hosts which makes the experience that much more pleasing. The menu is authentic Mediterranean and delicious. I recommend The Mediterranean Spot very highly. Check it out.
Friendly,  family-owned and great food.  Portions are huge.  Gyro meat is crispy and well seasoned. Best gyro platter in town.
Awesome!
